title: For Sale:  Custom 870
postcontent: I have a remington 870 super mag. The gun has been media blasted and coated in a bake on matte black paint that won't rust even when the finish is scratched off. The factory stock has been taken off and a hogue black over mold stock installed, the fore end was milled to fit the 3.5in chambered gun as there are no after market fore ends for a 3.5in gun to my knowlege. The choke is made by Jebbs and alone cost over 100 dollars to get made, they hold world records with their chokes. The barrel has been polished and the forcing cone slowly tuned to increase shot velocity and paternity uniformity. The reciever has been drilled and set up with a removable rail for any optics. The factory follower was swapped for a higher quality aluminum follower. If you are hunting turkey you must run an optic on the gun or you will miss the bird if it comes in closer than 30 yards. This gun and choke is set up for 40-65 yards. If you put on another choke you can open the close range pattern and get a good standard closer range shotgun. It shoots like a dream and I don't want to get rid of it but I have a new gun project I need to fund.
